"558","SUPPLEMENT DATED JULY 8, 2011"
"559","To the prospectuses dated February 28, 2011"
"560","The following text replaces the section of each"
"561","fund?s prospectus titled ?Exchanging shares?:"
"562","Exchanging shares"
"563","Generally You may exchange shares of the"
"564","fund for the same class of shares of other"
"565","funds sold by the distributor. For investors who"
"566","qualify as Clients of Eligible Financial"
"567","Intermediaries and participate in Eligible"
"568","Investment Programs made available through"
"569","their financial intermediaries (such as investors"
"570","in fee-based advisory or mutual fund ?wrap?"
"571","programs), an exchange may be made from"
"572","Class A or Class C shares to Class I shares of"
"573","the same fund under certain limited"
"574","circumstances. Please refer to the section of"
"575","this prospectus titled ?Retirement and"
"576","Institutional Investors ? eligible investors? or"
"577","contact your financial intermediary for more"
"578","information. An exchange of shares of one fund"
"579","for shares of another fund is considered a sale"
"580","and generally results in a capital gain or loss for"
"581","federal income tax purposes, unless you are"
"582","investing through an IRA, 401(k) or other tax-"
"583","advantaged account. An exchange of shares of"
"584","one class directly for shares of another class of"
"585","the same fund normally should not be taxable"
"586","for federal income tax purposes. You should"
"587","talk to your tax advisor before making an"
"588","exchange. The exchange privilege is not"
"589","intended as a vehicle for short-term trading. The"
"590","fund may suspend or terminate your exchange"
"591","privilege if you engage in a pattern of excessive"
"592","exchanges."
"593","Legg Mason offers a distinctive family of"
"594","funds tailored to help meet the varying needs"
"595","of large and small investors"
"596","You may exchange shares at their net asset"
"597","value next determined after receipt by your"
"598","Service Agent or the transfer agent of your"
"599","exchange request in good order. ? If you bought"
"600","shares through a Service Agent, contact your"
"601","Service Agent to learn which funds your Service"
"602","Agent makes available to you for exchanges ? If"
"603","you bought shares directly from the fund,"
"604","contact the fund at 1-877-721-1926 to"
"605","learn which funds are available to you for"
"606","exchanges ? Exchanges may be made only"
"607","between accounts that have identical"
"608","registrations ? Not all funds offer all classes?"
"609","Funds that offer Class B shares will continue to"
"610","make them available for incoming exchanges"
"611","after July 1, 2011? Some funds are offered only"
"612","in a limited number of states. Your Service"
"613","Agent or the fund will provide information about"
"614","the funds offered in your state"
"615","Always be sure to read the prospectus of the"
"616","fund into which you are exchanging shares."
"617","Investment minimums, sales charges and"
"618","other requirements"
"619","? In most instances, your shares will not be"
"620","subject to an initial sales charge or acontingent"
"621","deferred sales charge at the time of the"
"622","exchange"
"623","? Your contingent deferred sales charge (if any)"
"624","will continue to be measured from the date of"
"625","your original purchase of shares subject to a"
"626","contingent deferred sales charge,and you will be"
